```python
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
import numpy as np

# Prepare data for clustering
significant_supertypes = data_supertype_counts.index[:10]  # select top 10 supertypes for clarity
filtered_data = data[data['supertype'].isin(significant_supertypes)]

# Clustering using KMeans
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=10, random_state=0)
kmeans_labels = kmeans.fit_predict(filtered_data[['x', 'y']])
filtered_data['cluster'] = kmeans_labels

# Perform PCA for visualization
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
principal_components = pca.fit_transform(filtered_data[['x', 'y']])
filtered_data['PC1'] = principal_components[:, 0]
filtered_data['PC2'] = principal_components[:, 1]

# Visualize PCA results
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))
for i, supertype in enumerate(significant_supertypes):
    subset = filtered_data[filtered_data['supertype'] == supertype]
    plt.scatter(subset['PC1'], subset['PC2'], label=f'Supertype {supertype}', alpha=0.6)
plt.title('PCA of Spatial Clusters by Supertype')
plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
plt.legend()

plt.show()
```
